Amit Mehta said in his decision, and he determined it had gotten that way unfairly. It\u2019s a ruling that could portend big changes for the company, but we yet don\u2019t know how big, and we might not for years.</p>\n<p id=\"iBfcFs\">Mehta declared on Monday that Google was liable for violating antitrust laws, vindica", "id": 985960, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214641/google-us-monopoly-ruling-what-happens", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google Search is an illegal monopoly \u2014 what happens now?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T17:00:18+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Disney Plus ESPN Plus Hulu bundle\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8KTya30PiC_MdHmIZiZ4kSK_m5g=/0x51:1396x982/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73505049/disney_plus.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Disney</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aGVQEA\">The next phase of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/7/24150986/disney-streaming-business-earnings-q2-2024\">Disney\u2019s plan to make its streaming services profitable</a> is another round of price hikes served up with more news and new playlist features.</p>\n<p id=\"gdqKa1\">Disney is rolling out a new wave of price hikes that its subscribers will probably be none too pleased to be hit with. Beginning October 17th, individual monthly and annual plans for Disney Plus, Hulu, and ESPN are all going up. </p>\n  <figure class=\"e-image\">\n        \n  </figure>\n<p id=\"28GKQ5\">Monthly subscriptions to Disney Plus with ads will jump from $8 a month to $10. The monthly Disney Plus ad-free tier will i", "id": 985534, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214550/disney-plus-espn-and-hulu-october-price-hike", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Disney Plus, ESPN, and Hulu are all getting more expensive this October", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T17:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Waymo robotaxi in San Francisco\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TPKZRITTXqFo3w7Rq1AZBrWgp5U=/4x0:4924x3280/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73505030/2155631861.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Andrej Sokolow / picture alliance via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NSjUIh\">Waymo is spreading out a little more in the two major cities in which it operates. </p>\n<p id=\"AAKb5I\">The robotaxi company announced today that it was growing its service areas in both San Francisco and Los Angeles, as the company seeks to attract more customers to its burgeoning business. </p>\n<p id=\"Lc9nBv\">In San Francisco, Waymo\u2019s service area is extending south of the city into the San Francisco Peninsula to cover Daly City, Broadmoor, and Colma \u2014 a total of 10 additional square miles for a total of 55 square miles. The company recently <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24184814/waymo-waitlist-robotaxi-san-francisco-app-ride\">got ", "id": 985535, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214454/waymo-robotaxi-expand-service-area-sf-la-map", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Waymo is expanding its robotaxi service areas in San Francisco and Los Angeles", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T16:33:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the X logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/o_qZmYpHaC444Vw3xbJVIMgDFAo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504969/STK160_X_TWITTER_2__D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uV4Aj3\">X is suing a group of major advertisers over accusations that they held an \u201cillegal boycott\u201d against the platform formerly known as Twitter. In <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/25033219-x-vs-advertisers?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">a lawsuit filed on Tuesday</a>, X claims Unilever, Mars, CVS, \u00d8rsted, and dozens of other brands conspired to \u201ccollectively withhold billions of dollars in advertising revenue\u201d through a World Federation of Advertisers (WFA) industry initiative.</p>\n<p id=\"iU7oWm\">To join the WFA\u2019s initiative, called the Global Alliance for Responsible Media (GARM), companies must agree to withhold advertising from social platforms that aren\u2019t compliant wi", "id": 985536, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214536/x-elon-musk-antitrust-lawsuit-advertisers-boycott", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "X files antitrust lawsuit against advertisers over \u2018illegal boycott\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Crowdstrike logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/e5eXortGDCg00E8G41p4TAXpjR4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504859/STK275_CROWDSTRIKE_CVIRGINIA_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"W0BcFC\">Microsoft has responded to Delta Air Lines\u2019 criticism of Windows and CrowdStrike after the giant IT outage last month. Delta CEO Ed Bastian wants <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/1/24210680/crowdstrike-microsoft-outage-delta-lawsuit-class-action-damages\">compensation</a> from both CrowdStrike and Microsoft for the estimated $500 million Delta lost due to the outage. Now, Microsoft says Delta refused its free help on multiple occasions and even ignored an email from CEO Satya Nadella to Bastian.</p>\n<p id=\"Twa2Qy\">\u201cMicrosoft empathizes with Delta and its customers regarding the impact of the CrowdStrike incident. But your letter and Delta\u2019s public c", "id": 985041, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214371/microsoft-delta-letter-crowdstrike-response-comments", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u00a0says Delta ignored Satya Nadella\u2019s offer of CrowdStrike help", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T15:56:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Sonos Ace wireless headphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tdpyjcMXJvYdxfPHOzjVKmuNcGY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504849/DSCF7356_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jxz43H\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24169086/sonos-ace-headphones-review\">Sonos Ace headphones</a> launched with a very convenient trick called TV Audio Swap, which lets you send audio that would normally come out of the Sonos Arc soundbar to the headphones instead. Two months later, the company is enabling TV Audio Swap on its more affordable soundbars \u2014 and it\u2019s no longer limited to customers with Apple devices.</p>\n<p id=\"W2EuCY\">The feature now works on both generations of the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/27/17507796/sonos-beam-speaker-soundbar-alexa-review\">Sonos</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22701137/sonos-beam-gen-2-atmo", "id": 985042, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214510/sonos-ace-tv-audio-swap-beam-ray-android", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sonos brings TV Audio Swap to its more affordable soundbars \u2014 and Android", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T15:02:14+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An overhead image of the Chromecast with Google TV HD and its remote on a wooden table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3BUEh116kVk4XUoDeWDaz68MTVA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504751/ChromecastHDtable.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"t3GeYb\">Google is done making Chromecasts. In <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/google-nest/chromecast-history/\">a post on Tuesday</a>, Google says it\u2019s \u201cending production of Chromecast\u201d after over a decade of selling the streaming dongles.</p>\n<p id=\"kATytp\">Even though Chromecast devices will now be available \u201cwhile supplies last,\u201d Google says it will continue to push software and security updates to its newer devices without specifying which ones. The most recent update to the lineup was the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23395200/chromecast-google-tv-hd-review\">Chromecast with Google TV released in 2022</a>.", "id": 984501, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214471/google-chromecast-line-discontinued", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google is discontinuing the Chromecast line", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T14:02:13+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2WuaZDOpzmnnHEVckLbmAZtEyCw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504619/VST_0806_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NPf9gM\">The Quibi story is both short and epic. In January 2020, company founder Jeffrey Katzenberg and CEO Meg Whitman were onstage at CES delivering an hour-long presentation on how they were <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/1/8/21056315/quibi-ces-2020-launch-meg-whitman-jeffrey-katzenberg-turnstyle-technology-shows-preview\">about to upend the entertainment business</a>. They\u2019d developed new tech, signed up seemingly half the stars in Hollywood, and had raised more than a billion dollars to pull it off. By October, it was all over. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/10/22/21528404/quibi-shut-down-cost-subscribers-content-tv-movies-katzenberg-whitman-tiktok-netflix\">Quibi was shutting down</a>.</p>\n", "id": 984502, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24205146/quibi-history-ebooks-future-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Quibi\u2019s epic fall and the future of books", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:54:05+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Pixel 9 Pro Fold and Pixel 9 together\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CxlckqldwdDgntHAMpA1_b2zvbY=/0x0:1538x1025/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73493693/pixel_fold_9_google.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"lQuUSc\">Google\u2019s earlier-than-expected Pixel hardware event is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/25/24185767/google-pixel-hardware-ai-event-august-date\">just around the corner \u2014 it\u2019s scheduled for Tuesday, August 13th</a>. Thanks to the relentless flow of leaks that have emerged over the past few weeks, we have a pretty good idea of what to expect.</p>\n<p id=\"5yUCDi\">Google has already confirmed that it\u2019s launching the Pixel 9 and the Pixel 9 Pro Fold, but the company may have some other surprises in store, including the Buds Pro 2 and maybe even the Pixel Watch 3.</p>\n<p id=\"CI0DGJ\">Here\u2019s a roundup of everything we know so far.</p>\n<h2 id=\"ccKZ03\">Google ", "id": 984055, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/31/24208625/google-pixel-hardware-event-august-2024-leaks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What to expect from Google\u2019s Pixel 9 event", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:43:23+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"coffee machine with hot coffee cup, iced drink with hand pouring cream in, and sugar and coffee pods on a tray.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/38W29_uJwJvm-crQXdepSngHvR0=/3x0:2259x1504/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504512/Keurig_K_Brew_Chill_Lifestyle_090.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Hand required to add cream.</em> | Image: Keurig</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"D7AoEG\">I just used <a href=\"https://keurigdrpepper.com/quickchill-out-with-keurigs-new-k-brewchill/\">Keurig\u2019s new hybrid K-Brew and Chill</a> machine that can quickly cool down freshly brewed pod coffee (and fruity \u201crefreshers\u201d) to a temperature \u201cas cold as, if not colder,\u201d than an iced coffee and sweet drinks you could order at a local coffee shop. For me, there was something unexpectedly satisfying about making an instantly cold drink from a standalone and solidly built machine \u2014 even if the cup of La Colombe medium roast it made tasted disappointingly burn", "id": 984056, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24213299/keurig-k-brew-and-chill-coffee-maker-iced-cup", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Keurig\u2019s latest coffee brewer chills out drinks for the pod lovers", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:22:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic photo collage of Vice President Kamala Harris.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yRKabJOKvbKL-zRFkXVUxcdBrDw=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504479/STK205_KAMALA_HARRIS_CVIRGINIA_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XHfWg1\">Vice President Kamala Harris has chosen Minnesota Governor Tim Walz as her running mate in the 2024 presidential election, according to multiple news outlets <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/06/us/politics/kamala-harris-vp.html?smid=url-share\">including <em>The New York Times</em></a>. The news follows weeks of speculation during an accelerated campaign since President Joe Biden <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/21/24195289/biden-drops-out-presidential-election-race\">ended his candidacy and endorsed his VP for the role</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"WtasYU\">The choice comes weeks before the Democratic National Con", "id": 984057, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24210484/kamala-harris-vp-tim-walz-running-mate-minnesota", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Kamala Harris reportedly chooses Minnesota Governor Tim Walz as VP running mate", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A pink room with a figure near a Nest Thermostat on the wall and a smart speaker on a table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/08HowaUr9nGy7iiTyS8LJpp9vNs=/130x0:1071x627/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504381/Google_Home.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Google Home is getting a Gemini intelligence upgrade.</em> | Image: Google Nest</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap p-large-text\" id=\"0h8xCh\">While splashy chatbots may get all the attention, generative AI has real potential to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24177991/apple-intelligence-siri-voice-assistant-amazon-alexa-generative-ai\">make the smart home simpler and more accessible</a>. Amazon has already announced its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/20/23880764/amazon-ai-alexa-generative-llm-smart-home\">plans for a smarter Alexa</a> to power your home. Now, it\u2019s Google\u2019s turn to promise that it can produce a better, smarter, more helpful Googl", "id": 984059, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24213639/google-gemini-intelligence-ai-google-home-nest-aware", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Gemini intelligence is coming to Google Home", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the Nvidia logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/r2ZlpYpO34nYGP0nRL6gIuwjhXY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504384/STK083_NVIDIA_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CTntzs\">Nvidia is on a mission to eliminate its legacy Control Panel and GeForce Experience apps and combine them into a single new Nvidia app. That effort <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/22/24079529/nvidia-app-geforce-experience-control-panel-windows\">started earlier this year</a>, and a <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-us%2Fgeforce%2Fnews%2Fnvidia-app-beta-update-rtx-vsr-hdr-controls-and-more%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F8%2F6%2F24213585%2Fnvidia-app-update-rtx-video-display-features\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">new beta", "id": 984060, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24213585/nvidia-app-update-rtx-video-display-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nvidia\u2019s new app now has display settings, RTX Video HDR sliders, and more", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A marketing image of the Google TV Streamer.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/znrOeDFXcIAEdRVrsRHIU-3Pq1Q=/0x29:2040x1389/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504380/streamer.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Atr8jX\">Google isn\u2019t waiting for its upcoming hardware event to announce the Chromecast\u2019s successor. Alongside <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/e/23977579\">the new, sleeker Nest Thermostat</a>, today, the company is introducing the Google TV Streamer, a <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://store.google.com/product/google_tv_streamer?hl=en-US\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">$99.99 set-top box</a> that improves upon the Chromecast with Google TV with substantially better performance, Thread and Matter integration, and useful new features like a remote finder. </p>\n<p id=\"MNlnfO\">Yes, there are some Gemini AI tricks thrown in, and w", "id": 984058, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214055/google-tv-streamer-features-price-matter-thread", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Google TV Streamer might be the Apple TV 4K rival we\u2019ve been waiting for", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jXkdBnpzCm-M60sA0ceRwbfKRQM=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504386/247209_Google_Nest_Hardware_OGrove_0013.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Nest Learning Thermostat (4th gen) is a complete redesign of the iconic smart thermostat that first launched in 2011.</em> | Photo by Owen Grove / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap p-large-text\" id=\"jf96sB\">This week, almost a decade after Google last updated its flagship thermostat, the <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/google-nest/new-learning-thermostat/\">company has announced</a> the <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://store.google.com/us/product/nest_learning_thermostat_4th_gen?hl=en-US\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Nest Learning Thermostat (4th gen)</a>. The thermostat has an all-new design, several new features, and <a href=\"https://www.theve", "id": 984061, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24213538/google-nest-learning-thermostat-4th-gen-hands-on-price-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Nest Learning Thermostat gets its biggest upgrade in over a decade", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-06T12:16:11+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The CNET logo in red text against a white background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/a8ruLzODOntwV--BP6eZ0v37Dgs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504345/CNET_logo_red.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: CNET</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CV0I0z\">Red Ventures is selling CNET to Ziff Davis, the digital media and internet company that owns other notable tech publications like <em>Mashable</em>, <em>IGN</em>, and <em>Lifehacker</em>. Ziff Davis\u2019 chief executive, Vivek Shah, <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/08/06/business/media/cnet-ziff-davis.html\">confirmed the acquisition</a> to <em>The New York Times</em> on Tuesday.</p>\n<p id=\"apcXzs\">Ironically, back in 2000, it was CNET Networks Inc. that <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB963981866275420328\">paid $1.6 billion</a> to acquire the then-tech-publishing-behemoth Ziff-Davis Inc. and its online services company, ZDNet. So much has happened in the last tw", "id": 983596, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214374/cnet-zeff-davis-acquisition-digital-media-100-million", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Ziff Davis is 