873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73504131/thanossnap.0.gif\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: MacRumors (<a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://youtu.be/FzBa6Tc-JeE\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube</a>)</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"r9v0Q1\">Not a day goes by without me getting frustrated at the state of the mobile web. I rarely use my iPhone to read news articles now because every time I do there\u2019s a cookie prompt obstructing what I want to read, or so many ads on a page that I can\u2019t even see the text anymore. </p>\n<p id=\"dFYUHV\">Apple is clearly just as frustrated as I am, so it\u2019s added a Thanos snap animation to iOS 18 that wipes out annoying parts of websites.</p>\n<p id=\"GjYZvt\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/5/24213899/apple-safari-distraction-control-hide\">new \u201cDistraction Control\u201d feature</a> showed up in Safari earlier this week in the fifth beta of iO", "id": 982561, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/6/24214338/apple-ios-18-thanos-snap-animation-hide-ads", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "iOS 18 has fulfilled my dream of destroying ads with a Thanos snap", "user": null, "vote": 0}]